  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Prerequisite:</strong> Berserker sphere.</p>\n<p>You are not subject to fatigue or exhaustion that is the result of taking damage from environmental heat. In addition, while berserking or using the rage class feature, your body puts off an aura of heat affecting all creatures and objects within reach (including yourself). Each round that you continue berserking or raging, the heat severity level in the affected area increases by 1 step (maximum heat severity 4 + 1 step per 7 points of base attack bonus). Any round that you are not berserking or raging, the heat severity level in the affected area decreases by 1 step, until it has reached normal heat levels. For the purpose of control weather, you are considered to have a magic skill bonus equal to your base attack bonus.</p>\n",
